               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-309-person2536">
                  WILLIAM 
                  STODHARD
               <interp inst="t18300916-309-person2536" type="surname" value="STODHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-309-person2536" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-309-person2536" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18300916-309-viclabel1583" type="occupation">musician</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-309-victim2535 t18300916-309-viclabel1583"></join>, and live in Jerusalem-square, Hackney. On the 31st of July I was returning from Horslydown, where I had been engaged<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183009160133"></xptr>- I overtook the prisoner and another female; the prisoner laid hold of my right arm, and said, "Where are you going?" I said, "Home to my wife and family;" she said I had far better go home with her - I said I wished to have nothing to say to her, and knocked her hand away from me several times, but she laid hold of me again - she had left the other female; my money was in my righthand trousers pocket, which was not buttoned; she walked by my side some distance, began to relate a pitiful story, and wished me to give her something to drink - I said I had no objection if there was a house open, as I should like a glass myself; I went to a house about one hundred yards from <placeName id="t18300916-309-crimeloc1584">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-309-crimeloc1584" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-309-crimeloc1584" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-309-off1581 t18300916-309-crimeloc1584"></join>, and called for a quartern of gin - she poured out half a glass - I drank it, and received my change; I was going out - she extended her arm with the glass in it; I turned round, and saw the other female coming to take it - I went out instantly; she ran out, laid hold of my arm, and begged me to go with her - I said I would not, and turned away; she laid hold of my right arm, and tried to pull me another way - I laid hold of her arm, and her hand was in my pocket in a moment; I knocked it away, not thinking it had been deep enough to get my money - the other female came up - they communicated together; she said, "Be off, woman!" and then the other ran away - I felt in my pocket, missed my money, and charged her with it; she denied it - no money was found on her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-309-person2537">
                  JOHN 
                  HITCHCOCK
               <interp inst="t18300916-309-person2537" type="surname" value="HITCHCOCK"></interp>
